          I'm Enrique — everyone calls me Quique. I studied mathematics in Madrid and fell for
          the corner of it where geometry meets rigour: my bachelor's thesis walks from the
          Morse Lemma to the Morse inequalities, following Milnor's <em>Morse Theory</em>.
          These days I write mathematics a computer checks line by line, in Lean 4, working
          towards manifolds and Mathlib.
        </p>
        <p>
          By day I process fNIRS and EEG recordings — Python, MNE, real messy data under real
          hardware constraints. A different world with the same instinct: take something that
          looks like intuition and make it <em>rigorous</em>.
        </p>
        <p>
          I also co-organize <a href="https://madlean-hub.web.app">MadLean</a>, Madrid's Lean
          community. This site is my notebook — imperfect notes published while I learn,
          especially where Lean meets AI. Poke around.
